    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-22T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="1222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6266A/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-22T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 22, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 22—10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2577. This is Tittmann’s 126, April 8, reference Department’s 917, March 20 to
                        Bern.<note n="60a" xml:id="d1222fn1">See footnote 59, above.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I should like to notify Holy See of our attitude but before doing so I would like
                    to be certain that it is our intention to give enemy diplomats <pb facs="1326"
                        n="1316" xml:id="pg_1316"/> accredited to Holy See option of <hi
                        rend="italic">leaving Rome altogether</hi> or of moving into Vatican City.
                    Although this seems to be implied in paraphrase of telegram received here it is
                    not entirely clear. Please confirm by telegram. [Tittmann.]</p>
                <p>Legation note: paraphrase was clear rendition of original.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
